LDS._0984_01_Tu_QUE_LIB_SIN_SU_COS_VOL__ETI_["eng"] = u"(This book is called: \"On Conscience Vol.1 - Ethics\"...)"
LDS._0984_02_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol1Etica__LA_CUL_DI_CUI_LET__FON_SI_CRE_E_SI_EVO_NEG_ESS_VIV_QUA_QUE_CRE_E_FAN_ESP_TAN_PI_DUE_ANI_SON_IN_CON_TAN_PI_LA_LOR_ESP_E_QUI_ANC_LA_LOR_CUL__COM_["eng"] = u"... Culture, of which ethics is the foundation, is created and evolves in living beings when they grow up and experience it. The more two animals interact, the more their experience, and therefore their culture, is shared..."
LDS._0984_03_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol1Etica__NEL_MOM_IN_CUI_LE_CIR_IMP_UNA_CON_TRA_ANI_CON_CUL_DIV__NEC_CHE_NAS_UNA_NUO_CUL_E_TAL_UNA_NUO_ETI_COM_FRU_DEL_DEL_PRE_SPE_PER_LIM_NEL_A_UNA_CUL_CON_UNE_MOL_DIF_PU_RIC_SFO_CHE_NON_VOG_ESS_ACC_SON_QUE_I_CAS_IN_CUI_POS_NAS_SCO_["eng"] = u"... At times when circumstances require animals with different cultures to coexist, it is necessary that a new culture - and sometimes a new ethic - should born as a result of the union of the previous ones. However, the commitment to adapt to a culture with a very different ethic often require efforts that one may not want to accept. These are the cases in which clashes can arise..."
LDS._0984_04_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol1Etica__NEL_PEN_DI_ALC_NEL_MOM_IN_CUI_ESI_UNA_SOL_CUL_CON_DA_TUT_SAR_FIN_CHI_QUA_SIA_LA_GIU_ETI__SCO_DI_QUE_FAN_ESP_LE_PRO_CRE_PRE_GLI_ALT_ANC_ATT_LUS_DEL_FOR_["eng"] = u"... Some may think that if there is going to be a universal culture - one culture shared by all - it will finally be clear what the right ethic is. It is the aim of these fanatics to project their beliefs onto others, including through the use of force..."
LDS._0984_05_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol1Etica__OSS_UNO_SCO_TRA_DUE_FAZ_CON_RIS_IRR_E_INS_DOM_QUA_DEL_DUE_ABB_TOR_OGN__IL_MAL_DEL_POI_OGN__GIU_TRA_LE_REG_ETI_DEL_["eng"] = u"... While observing a clash between two opposing factions, it is irrelevant and pointless asking which one is wrong: each is the evil side of the other since each is judged by the ethical rules of the other..."
LDS._0984_06_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol1Etica__NON_PU_ESI_CON_TRA_CUL_INC_QUI_NON_PU_ESI_UNE_OGG_GIU_E_NON_ESI_NEA_NEL_MOM_IN_CUI_NE_RIM_UNA_QUE_CHE_RIS_VIN_DOV_LA_SUA_SOP_ALL_DEI_SUO_SOS_NON_ALL_SUA_OGG_["eng"] = u"... There can be no reconciliation between irreconcilable cultures, so there can be no objectively correct ethics. And it will not exist even if only one of them prevails: the one that survives will owe its survival to the aggressiveness of its supporters, not to its objectivity."
LDS._0984_07_Tu_MMH_["eng"] = u"... <*>#italic#Mmm...<*>"
LDS._0985_01_Tu_QUE_LIB_SIN_SU_COS_VOL__LIB_ARB_["eng"] = u"(This book is called: \"On Conscience Vol.2 - Free Will\"...)"
LDS._0985_02_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol2LiberoArbitrio__PER_DIS_SUL_LIB_ARB__INN_NEC_DIS_DUE_POS_LA_PRI__QUE_IN_CUI_SI_RIT_CHE_TUT_CI_CHE_ESI__COS_DA_MAT_LA_SEC_INV__QUE_IN_CUI_SI_COS_POS_LES_DI_ELE_NON_MAT_TRA_CUI_RIE_LAN_COM_MOT_DI_OGN_ESS_VIV_["eng"] = u"... In order to discuss free will it is mandatory to distinguish between two possibilities: the first one, in which it is believed that everything that exists is made up of matter; and the second one, in which the existence of non-material elements is considered possible - included the soul, as the motor of every living being..."
LDS._0985_03_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol2LiberoArbitrio__DEC_DI_PER_LA_PRI_IPO__CHI_CHE_NON_PU_ESS_LIB_ARB_ALL_STE_MOD_IN_CUI__POS_CAL_AZ_DI_OGG_INA_SAR_POS_CAL_LE_AZI_DEG_ESS_ANI_LUN_DIF_TRA_LE_DUE_CAT_RIM_LA_PRE_NEL_SEC_RAG_DEL_COS_A_CUI_LA_PAR_VI_RID_TUT_IL_SUO_SIG_["eng"] = u"... As for the first hypothesis, it is clear that there could never be free will: just as it is possible to calculate the \"actions\" of inanimate objects, it will be possible to calculate the actions of animated beings as well. The only difference between the two categories would be the presence - in the second one - of consciousness, to which the word \"life\" relies all its meaning."
LDS._0985_04_LibroSullaCoscienzaVol2LiberoArbitrio__PER_LA_SEC_IPO_INV__VER_CHE_LAN_NON_SAR_GOV_DAL_STE_LEG_DEL_MAT_MA_DA_QUE_LEG_COM_DIP_IL_COM_DEG_IND_COS_COM_IL_LOR_PEN_VIE_PLA_DAL_CHE_GLI_STE_COM_SUL_MON_MAT_LAN_VER_IN_QUE_MOD_INF_E_CO_DAL_MAT_RIS_QUI_NON_PI_LIB_["eng"] = u"... As for the second hypothesis, it is true that the soul would not be ruled by the same laws of matter, but it would still rely on these same laws. The behavior of individuals, as well as their thought, is shaped by the experience that they gather in the material world. The soul would thus be affected and \"corrupted\" by matter, thus being no longer free."
